body:
✨Capture It, Remember It!✨

Hey Taylor,

I hope that you are having fun on tour and meeting up with so many swifties as well. I would like to say that I AM GOING TO SEE YOU IN CONCERT AS WELL WITH MY CLOSE FRIEND NICK! We are both extremely excited and can not wait for JULY 22ND to come soon enough. We will be in SECTION 118 ROW 22 SEATS 21 & 22; it would be off to the side of your B Stage (the one you perform Dress on). And of course we both would love to meet you as well and that this will be Nick’s FIRST TIME seeing you in concert!

Personally, Taylor- I have been listening to your music since the very first time I have heard and seen the music video for, OUR SONG on CMT! Its crazy to think that it has been 11 years since that song came out and changed my life forever! I never thought in that moment, I would need someone as special and amazing as you to help me grow and become such a better person. Throughout each album listening to your songs and watching the music videos through out the years - it feels like I grew up with you for those 11 years. Still can’t believe that I have been a Swiftie for those 11 years and I truly am happy that you are truly happy after all those years. Taylor, those 11 years you helped me realized that everything will be okay in the end of the all the endings. You helped me through a friendship that had its ups and downs - with the song Out of the Woods; making me realize that people are going to be Mean no matter how nice you are to them; helping me Shake It Off when things get tough; helped me be Clean after a toxic friendship; making me wish that I will Never Grow Up and deal with the real world; and realize that some people aren’t worth my time because This Is Why We Can’t Have Nice Things… Taylor, there are so many songs that helped me through my darkest days and you were always there to put a smile face when it needed it the most. I could go on and on, but that it would never end, just like my love for you. I Love You Taylor Swift! And thank you for everything and even more!

Also, I had the opportunity to see in concert for the FIRST TIME during The 1989 World Tour at MetLife Stadium Night 2 with my older sister as a Christmas Gift. I truly cried like a baby seeing you come out on that stage for the first time ever!

Overall, if I was able to meet you with my close friend, Nick- it would truly be an experience that I would remember for the rest of my life. I would truly hold onto the memories for as long as I live!

Just A Reminder: Nick and I would be sitted in SECTION 118; ROW 22; Seats 21 & 22 on July 22nd at MetLife Stadium screaming/singing along to all the song and dancing like nobody is watching!

We love you Tay-Tay! See you July 22nd at MetLife Stadium Night 3!

Love, Jackie 💜

blog.name: babywerethe-newromantics
blog.title: abi
blog.description: Had the pleasure of meeting Taylor, the queen, herself and I am so grateful for that moment.

body:
PLEASE READ AND SHARE

@taylorswift

Basically, I’ll keep it brief, I’m the worst friend because throwback to June 2016, I went to a taylor Swift concert with my friend who comes to all the concerts with me. But, I had the opportunity for a back stage tour and I accepted, knowing I had to leave my friend alone (we gave the spare ticket to another friend so not completely alone), for the concert and sit in better seats. The tour person comes out and it’s ANDREA SWIFT, TAYLORS FREAKING MOTHER, anyway, I died, came back to life, did the tour and Andrea picked me to meet Taylor.

Hopefully that explains why I’d give anything for my friend to receive any form of communication fromTaylor Swift.

So, please please please, make me being a bad friend into a little bit less of a bad friend. She also deserves it sooo much. She’s the most selfless I know, she’s currently training to be a nurse and I’m so so so proud of her for that!

Her name is Caitlin Newton and we are coming to both Manchester shows and both London shows.

Please share this and get this to Taylor, I will do anything, even die. I mean, ive met Taylor, life doesn’t get better than that!
